# Chat UX bans (do not reintroduce)

When the user says **remove**, leave it removed. Do **not** bring these back in later PRs,
“polish”, FEATURES grade-ups, or “parity” work.

## 1. No “Recalled N memories” chip
- Do **not** show a recalled / “✨ Recalled N memories” (or similar) chip on assistant messages.
- Backend may still send `recalled` for logging/metrics; the **mobile UI must not surface it**.
- Do not wire `showRecalledMemories`, `chat.recalled_memories`, or equivalent UI again.

## 2. No Show more / Show less on LLM (assistant) message bodies
- Assistant markdown/text must **not** fold with Show more / Show less.
- Keep `CollapsibleMessageBody` **`collapsible={false}`** for assistant bubbles (or omit folding).
- **Exception:** code blocks may keep their own Show more / Show less (`CodeBlock`).
- User-message folding is separate; do not “fix parity” by enabling assistant folding again.

When the user says **remove**, leave it removed. Do **not** bring these back in later PRs,
“polish”, FEATURES grade-ups, or “parity” work.

## 3. No project filter chips on Lists / Todos
- Do **not** show a horizontal chip row to filter todos by Learning project on the Lists screen.
- Linking a todo to a project (folder on a row) may remain; the top filter bar must not return.

If a plan or FEATURES item asks for these, **push back and skip** — they are explicitly rejected.
